(43, 7, 37, 66, 22, 17, 17, NULL, 'Invitation to Drink Water', 'Both passages emphasize an invitation to those who are thirsty to come and receive water. This connection highlights the theme of spiritual nourishment and the offer of life-giving water.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 37, 19, 42, 2, 2, 'thirst', 'Thirst for God', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual thirst present in both passages. In John 7:37, Jesus invites those who thirst to come to Him, paralleling the longing expressed in Psalms 42:2 for the living God.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 37, 66, 21, 6, 6, 'If any man thirst, let him come', 'Connection of Thirst and Water', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of thirst and the offer of life-giving water. Jesus invites those who thirst to come and drink, while Revelation promises the water of life to the thirsty.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 38, 23, 12, 3, 3, 'out of his belly shall flow rivers of living water', 'Living Water and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of drawing water, symbolizing spiritual sustenance. John 7:38 speaks of ''rivers of living water,'' while Isaiah 12:3 mentions ''wells of salvation,'' connecting the concepts of faith and divine provision.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 38, 23, 44, 3, 3, 'rivers of living water', 'Living Water and Thirst', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of water as a source of life and blessing. John 7:38 speaks of ''rivers of living water'' flowing from believers, while Isaiah 44:3 mentions pouring water on the thirsty, linking spiritual nourishment to physical thirst.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 38, 43, 4, 10, 10, 'living water', 'Living Water Theme Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''living water.'' John 7:38 speaks of rivers of living water flowing from believers, while John 4:10 refers to Jesus offering living water to the Samaritan woman. This connection highlights the significance of spiritual sustenance in Jesus'' teachings.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 38, 20, 10, 11, 11, 'living water', 'Connection of Life and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of life flowing from the righteous. Both passages emphasize the idea of life-giving qualities, with ''rivers of living water'' in John and ''well of life'' in Proverbs.', 'theme', 0.839, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 38, 38, 14, 8, 8, NULL, 'Living Waters Connection', 'Both passages emphasize ''living waters'' flowing from a source. John 7:38 speaks of believers as conduits of living water, while Zechariah 14:8 describes living waters flowing from Jerusalem. This connection highlights a shared theme of spiritual sustenance.', 'theme', 0.8109999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 38, 20, 18, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Living Water and Wisdom', 'This connection highlights the imagery of flowing water in both passages. John 7:38 speaks of ''rivers of living water,'' while Proverbs 18:4 describes ''deep waters'' and a ''flowing brook,'' suggesting a thematic link between spiritual nourishment and wisdom.', 'theme', 0.762, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 38, 48, 5, 22, 23, 'rivers of living water', 'Connection of Living Water and Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual sustenance. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of belief and the resulting fruits of the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.72, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
