(43, 7, 40, 43, 1, 21, 21, 'this is the Prophet', 'Recognition of the Prophet', 'This connection highlights the people''s recognition of Jesus as ''the Prophet'' in John 7:40, paralleling the inquiry about ''that prophet'' in John 1:21. Both passages emphasize the significance of prophetic identity in relation to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 40, 43, 6, 14, 14, NULL, 'Recognition of the Prophet', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of Jesus as ''the Prophet.'' This connection highlights the people''s acknowledgment of Jesus'' identity following His miracles and teachings.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 41, 43, 7, 52, 52, 'Shall Christ come out of Galilee?', 'Galilee and Prophetic Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the skepticism surrounding Jesus'' identity as the Christ due to his Galilean origin. The mention of Galilee in both verses highlights a perceived limitation regarding prophetic authority.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 41, 43, 1, 46, 46, 'Shall Christ come out of Galilee?', 'Connection of Skepticism about Christ', 'Both passages emphasize doubt regarding Jesus'' origins. In John 7:41, some question if the Christ can come from Galilee, while in John 1:46, Nathanael expresses skepticism about anything good coming from Nazareth.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 41, 40, 16, 14, 16, 'This is the Christ', 'Recognition of Christ''s Identity', 'This connection highlights the differing opinions about Jesus'' identity in both passages. In John 7:41, some question if the Christ can come from Galilee, while in Matthew 16:16, Peter declares Jesus as the Christ, affirming his identity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 41, 43, 4, 25, 25, 'This is the Christ', 'Connection of Messianic Expectation', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Christ. In John 7:41, some question if Christ can come from Galilee, while in John 4:25, the woman acknowledges the coming of the Messiah, who is identified as Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 41, 43, 6, 69, 69, 'this is the Christ', 'Recognition of Christ''s Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of Jesus as the Christ. In John 7:41, some question if the Christ can come from Galilee, while John 6:69 affirms belief in Jesus as the Christ, the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
